args: I heard from the others about how you\nstuck with me while I was suffering from\namnesia. Thank you.
It was no big deal. We just relaxed on the\nbeach together.
Would you...tell me about what happened\nbefore my memories came back?
The whole incident is hazy to me,\nlike a fleeting dream.
...No matter what's going on, you're always\nthe same {player_name}.
Ahem. Just talking to myself. Now, you\nwanted to know what happened? No sweat.
Let me think... First, we had some food at\nthe cafe.
Your amnesia hit suddenly, and we\nwere both very worried. I thought eating\nsomething good would cheer you up.
It feels like a waste to not remember\nwhat I ate.
Then we'll just have to go tomorrow\nand order it again. Anyway, after we\nate, we went for a walk on the beach.
We came upon some locals making\nwishing crystals, and you joined in.
So that's what the crystal next to me\nwas. They're supposed to float once\nthey've been filled with wishes, right?
So why was mine left behind, lying inert?
Mym... Will you tell me how you feel?
You might well be happy if you stayed\nlike this, swaddled in sweet oblivion.
If you wanted it, I could fly us both\nsomewhere far away. It would be nice.\nBut...
That would be to deny who you have been\nall along.
Love is putting your beloved's feelings\nat the forefront. And that's why all my\nhesitation is gone now.
Wait, is that what I think it is?
Wishing crystal, grant me my wish.
Thank you, my love. It made me so happy\nto hear you confess your feelings for me.
Huh? Oh, um... Where were we?
I asked why the crystal I made was\nleft behind. Are...you okay, though?\nYou suddenly spaced out.
I'm fine. I was just thinking back a bit.\nIf I recall, when you went to raise the\ncrystal into the air, you collapsed.
That's why it was left as it was. I was\nrelieved that your memories were back\nwhen you awakened.
It sounds like you went to a lot of\ntrouble for me. Thank you.
I did what anyone would do.\nYou mean the world to me.
Ha ha! And you to me, Mym.
(I know he means he cares about me as\na friend—a comrade.)
(I'm the one who chose for things to be\nlike this. I'm fine with this...)
Mym... You mean the world to me.
(Come on, Mym, get it together! When\nhe had lost his memory, he conveyed his\nfeelings despite his unease.)
(I need to do the same thing and just say\nit. What is it that I desire? Don't let it end\nas nothing more than a wish!)
Hey, I know. Since we have it, let's go\nahead and try to get this crystal to float.
That's all right. I have to make my wishes\ncome true myself.
And not in the way you care for me—\nlike, as a friend.
I want to spend my life with you.\nI want to be your number one.
Can you say the same? Do you love me\nin a way that goes beyond the bounds of\nfriend and comrade?
...I'm sorry. I can't answer that on the spot.
Maybe I'm not mature enough to\nunderstand what it means to be in love.

And honestly, right now... I can't think
about it. I need to focus on me. Because
if I can't love myself, how am I supposed
to love somebody else?

And so long as my mind's a mire of half-
considered thoughts and emotions, I don't
think I can give your feelings the level of
consideration they deserve. I'm sorry.
It's fine. I somehow knew that's where\nyou'd be at with all of this.
But don't worry. I'm a dragon, after all!
And we dragons live a long time.\nI can wait patiently for your answer.
If you can give me an answer once you've\ndone some growing and exploring in the\nrealm of love, that's good enough for me.
And so, my darling—\ndon't ever forget this summer.
I promise you I won't.\nNo matter what happens.
(I'm not going to lose confidence ever\nagain, so long as I remember the promise\nwe made this summer.)
(I'll be waiting for you, darling. Always.)
